06:04.791 --> 06:06.797
I mean, 'cause you could totally say no.

06:06.822 --> 06:08.366
I mean, why would you wanna...

06:08.402 --> 06:11.403
(LIKE OLD MAN): hang out
with an old guy like me?

06:11.438 --> 06:13.204
Come on, bud, five minutes.

06:13.240 --> 06:14.949
Just, you know, four.

06:14.974 --> 06:16.774
May-Maybe-maybe two.

06:18.704 --> 06:19.870
Right on.

06:20.411 --> 06:22.211
Whatever.

06:23.466 --> 06:25.838
Hey. Thanks for watching Dawn.

06:25.863 --> 06:27.096
Of course.

06:27.398 --> 06:29.120
I should warn you that Carol

06:29.145 --> 06:31.907
was not too thrilled
about me being pulled away.

06:31.932 --> 06:33.358
Oh, God. What now?

06:33.393 --> 06:35.260
She's just mad because she thinks

06:35.295 --> 06:38.463
I spend more time with
Dawn than with the twins.

06:38.498 --> 06:40.198
Well, you're Dawn's mom, too.

06:40.233 --> 06:42.233
Oh, not according to Carol.

06:42.269 --> 06:45.270
She's giving me grief on
account of us not being married.

06:45.305 --> 06:47.272
- Oh!
- You know Carol. I mean,

06:47.307 --> 06:48.540
she won't go to the bathroom

06:48.575 --> 06:51.309
unless she's got a
certified dumping permit.

06:51.345 --> 06:52.344
Yeah.

06:53.201 --> 06:54.848
(LAUGHS)

06:54.873 --> 06:56.673
(CHUCKLES): What?

06:57.484 --> 07:00.904
I was just thinking about
us as a married couple.

07:01.108 --> 07:02.520
(LAUGHS)

07:02.556 --> 07:04.589
What's so funny about that?

07:04.843 --> 07:08.622
I mean, can you imagine <i>
us</i> getting all gussied up

07:08.647 --> 07:12.615
and declaring our love to the
world like a couple of chumps?

07:12.640 --> 07:13.806
(LAUGHS)

07:13.831 --> 07:15.748
Yeah, wouldn't that be horrible?

07:17.954 --> 07:19.998
What? Did I say s...

07:21.375 --> 07:23.341
(GROANS)

07:23.908 --> 07:25.107
Women.

07:28.114 --> 07:29.980
Okay, hun, look,

07:30.015 --> 07:32.149
I'm sorry... I didn't mean it that way.

07:32.184 --> 07:33.984
- Sure.
- I mean,

07:34.019 --> 07:36.253
it's not that I wouldn't
want to be married to you,

07:36.288 --> 07:39.458
I just don't want to
be married to anybody.

07:39.483 --> 07:41.583
It's a flawed institution.

07:41.608 --> 07:43.475
It's like bread bowls

07:43.500 --> 07:46.804
or... the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame.

07:46.829 --> 07:48.945
You already made your point,
so could we just drop it?

07:48.970 --> 07:52.712
I mean, we live together,
we're raising a kid together.

07:52.737 --> 07:54.771
It's like we're already married.

07:54.796 --> 07:58.142
The only thing we don't have is
just some stupid piece of paper.

07:58.177 --> 08:00.978
Yeah, stupid piece of paper...

08:01.013 --> 08:04.014
that says you'll always be
there even if the other person

08:04.049 --> 08:07.885
gets sick or they get fat or
they... drool in their sleep,

08:08.303 --> 08:10.378
because you can't imagine
your life without them.

08:10.403 --> 08:13.237
(GROANS): Oh, God. All right.

08:14.535 --> 08:18.896
If getting married is really
something that you want to do,

08:18.931 --> 08:22.099
then... I'll bite the bullet.

08:22.134 --> 08:26.003
Wow. With a proposal like
that, how could I say no?

08:30.712 --> 08:32.142
Whoa! Oops.

08:32.178 --> 08:34.178
Must be a hole in my glove.

08:34.563 --> 08:37.313
Oh! Uh-oh, worm burner! (CHUCKLES)

08:37.597 --> 08:39.934
Hey, you know, truth be told,

08:39.960 --> 08:42.481
I never even played
catch... It's just something

08:42.506 --> 08:45.255
I saw all my friends do
with <i> their</i> dads, and...

08:45.749 --> 08:48.225
Well, my dad was a
little checked out, so...

08:48.260 --> 08:50.227
I taught myself how to play catch,

08:50.405 --> 08:52.396
how to ride a bike, you know?

08:52.421 --> 08:55.199
Um... even taught myself how to shave.

08:55.234 --> 08:57.100
What's to shave?

08:57.606 --> 08:59.773
Oh, you don't know about shaving?

08:59.931 --> 09:02.206
Ah, bud, learning to shave is...

09:02.241 --> 09:04.007
like a rite of passage.

09:04.043 --> 09:06.843
It'd be my honor to
guide you through it.

09:06.912 --> 09:08.845
Here, give me that.

09:08.881 --> 09:10.881
Go long. (CHUCKLES)

09:11.350 --> 09:13.317
No. Not <i> that</i> long, bud.

09:18.123 --> 09:19.923
Thanks again, Melissa.

09:19.959 --> 09:21.225
Gail said she was gonna help,

09:21.260 --> 09:24.261
